SYNOPSIS
        varargs int invalid_name(string sName)
        
DESCRIPTION
        The efun returns 1 for an invalid name sent to the efun.
        The efun returns -1 if the name is less then 3 characters
          long, or more then 11 characters long.
        The efun returns -2 if the name contains a special character
          like '?!~<>+_'
        The efun returns -3 if the name is already in use or banished.
        The efun returns -4 if the profanity filter catches it.
        The efun returns 0 otherwise, and the name is acceptable.

